The paper discusses the performance of applications on emerging hybrid-memory systems, which involves aspects of computer architecture, distributed computing, software engineering, databases, and human-computer interaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Architecture), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
